# ColorStop

**Object**

The object for specifying the color and location for a color stop in a gradient.

## Declaration

```swift
object ColorStop
```

## Discussion

Use this object for gradients in a [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/LinearGradientFill] style definition.

### Example

```json
{
  "components": [
    {
      "role": "container",
      "layout": {
        "ignoreDocumentMargin": true,
        "minimumHeight": "50vh"
      },
      "style": {
        "fill": {
          "type": "linear_gradient",
          "angle": -10,
          "colorStops": [
            {
              "color": "#FFFFFF",
              "location": 0
            },
            {
              "color": "#FFFFFF",
              "location": 20
            },
            {
              "color": "#AAAAAA",
              "location": 50
            },
            {
              "color": "#333333",
              "location": 90
            },
            {
              "color": "#000000",
              "location": 100
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "components": [
        {
          "role": "body",
          "textStyle": {
            "textColor": "#FFFFFF"
          },
          "text": "Fade to black."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Backgrounds for Components

- **Applying a Background to a Component**: Change the appearance of the backgrounds in your article.
- **ImageFill**: The object for adding an image background fill to a component.
- **RepeatableImageFill**: The object for adding a background image that Apple News can repeat.
- **VideoFill**: The object for adding a video background fill to a component.
- **LinearGradientFill**: The object for displaying a linear gradient as a component background.
- **GradientFill**: The properties all gradient fill types share.
- **Fill**: The object for setting a fill type and attachment for a component’s background fill.
